data.content:
Yes! In MSTest 3.7+, you can use **ValueTuples** instead of `object[]` for type-safe dynamic data:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
[DynamicData(nameof(TestData))]
public void Validate_ReturnsExpected(string input, bool expected)
{
    var result = Validator.IsValid(input);
    Assert.AreEqual(expected, result);
}

public static IEnumerable<(string input, bool expected)> TestData =>
[
    ("valid@email.com", true),
    ("invalid", false),
    ("", false),
];
```

**Benefits:**
- Compile-time type checking (no `object[]` casts)
- Named tuple elements serve as documentation
- Refactoring-safe — adding/changing a parameter type causes a compiler error instead of a runtime failure

This requires **MSTest 3.7+**. The test method signature stays the same; MSTest automatically destructures the tuple into the method parameters.
